Stephen C. Meyer - Wikipedia






















 






Stephen C. Meyer

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search

This article is about the Intelligent design advocate. For the rugby player, see Steve Meyer.


Stephen C. Meyer





Born
1958 (age 58–59)
USA


Alma mater
University of Cambridge


Occupation
Director of the Center for Science and Culture at the Discovery Institute and Vice President and Senior Fellow at the DI


Known for
Advocate of intelligent design


Website
www.stephencmeyer.org


Stephen C. Meyer (born 1958) is an advocate of intelligent design. He helped found the Center for Science and Culture (CSC) of the Discovery Institute (DI), which is the main organization behind the intelligent design movement.[1][2][3] Before joining the DI, Meyer was a professor at Whitworth College. Meyer is currently a Senior Fellow of the DI and Director of its Center for Science and Culture (CSC).[4]



Contents


1 Biography
2 Work

2.1 Intelligent Design
2.2 Films & Debates
2.3 Teach the Controversy
2.4 Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington article
2.5 Claims of persecution
2.6 Signature in the Cell
2.7 Darwin's Doubt


